Humans have value and can solve human problems;

 Science, free speech, rational thought, democracy, and freedom in the arts go together; 

 There is nothing supernatural.

Commitment to the application of reason and science to the understanding of the universe and to the solving of human problems;

 Opposition to denigrating human intelligence, seeking to explain the world in supernatural terms, looking outside nature for salvation;

 A belief that scientific discovery and technology can contribute to the betterment of human life;

 A belief in an open and pluralistic society and that democracy is the best guarantee of protecting human rights from authoritarian elites and repressive majorities;

 Commitment to the principle of the separation of church and state. 

 These are only a few of Secular Humanist values. I can list more, if you like.
